doc_summary_long: Milwaukee County Sheriff David A. Clarke Jr. said Wednesday he would leave office next month to accept a federal appointment as an assistant secretary in the U.S. Department of Homeland Security. In a tweet, the Department of Homeland Security said no announcement had been made on any appointment involving Clarke. Clarke will work for Homeland Security Secretary John Kelly, a retired Marine general.
doc_summary_short: Milwaukee County Sheriff David A. Clarke Jr. said Wednesday he would leave office next month to accept a federal appointment as an assistant secretary in the U.S. Department of Homeland Security.
doc_title: Milwaukee County Sheriff David Clarke says he's taking job in Department of Homeland Security
